cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper deals with age estimation and brain morphology using machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image analysis and feature extraction from neuroimaging databases. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper proposes an alternative approach to age estimation using Gaussian process regression models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques applied to brain morphology analysis. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with brain morphology and age estimation, which are related to neuroscience. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with brain morphology analysis, which could have implications for human-computer interaction.
